Rating: 3
Yum. Personally, I think the sauce needed to be thickened slightly before adding the plums and serving. As it stands, the sauce is quite runny, and mixes with other flavours on the plate . . . okay if you plan for it . . . I actually soaked my plums in the alcohol for 24 hours before poaching and it was still fine. Quite yummy.

Rating: 4
OK. So I did a different version of this pork using my slow cooker. I made the sauce as written, but didn't strain or reduce. Took 1/2 the mixture and put it in the cooker with my pork. Cooked it on low overnight. In the morning I took the pork out and dumped the juice/sauce. I then strained and reduced the other 1/2 of the sauce, pulled the pork, and put them back in the slow cooker for an hour to fuse. The results were fabulous! Even my kids loved it! And... so easy. Enjoy!

