Rating: 3
This was delicious. I usually don't like when people write about all the substitutions they made, but we used a California Sauvignon Blanc for the white and were a bit short on the broth--other than that, it was the same. I mention it only because when we reduced to the 1 cup level, it was a bit thin and lacking. Once we continued reducing, it got syrupy and was so yummy. Be patient, and it will be worth it!